etymologies: late Middle English: from medieval Latin sagittalis, from Latin sagitta ‘arrow’

definitions: relating to or denoting the suture on top of the skull which runs between the parietal bones in a front to back direction.
shortDefinitions: of suture on top of skull which runs between parietal bones in front

definitions: of or in a plane parallel to the sagittal suture, especially that dividing the body into left and right halves
shortDefinitions: of or in plane parallel to sagittal suture
